  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 679 (hl3481): __enter__, __exit__, __call__ dict-presence checks for hashlib/uuid/struct/socket types."
    - "All values False."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __enter__, __exit__, or __call__ in its own __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not implement context-manager or callable protocols."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no enter/exit/call defined in its own __dict__."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

